OL,3,CDoes rugby union owe rugby league an
OL,4,Capology?
OL,6,FThe split between rugby union and
OL,7,Frugby league came about in 1895. It
OL,8,Fwas disagreements over professionalism
OL,9,Fthat drove the division.
OL,11,FClubs in the north of England wanted
OL,12,Fto pay players to compensate them for
OL,13,Ftime missed at work (known as broken-
OL,14,Ftime payments). Frustrated by the
OL,15,FRugby Football Union's strict
OL,16,Famateurism and opposition to
OL,17,Fprofessionalism, they formed the
OL,18,FNorthern Rugby Football Union (which
OL,19,Flater became the Rugby Football
OL,20,FLeague).
