OL,6,FThose who make it to the top, while
OL,7,Fthey seldom play for their home sides
OL,8,Fthese days, are placed on a pedestal.
OL,9,FProfessional union players are
OL,10,Fhometown heroes, while us mere mortals
OL,11,Fbeam with pride at our claim on them.
OL,13,FAdmittedly, it wasn't until I left the
OL,14,Fborders that I realised not everyone
OL,15,Fshares a hometown with rugby royalty.
