OL,6,FI spoke to professor Tony Collins, a
OL,7,Fleading rugby historian, who had a few
OL,8,Fideas about why these border players
OL,9,Fswitched code.
OL,11,FObviously, it was a chance to be paid
OL,12,Fto do something they love. In tough
OL,13,Feconomic times and young families to
OL,14,Fprovide for - being paid thousands for
OL,15,Fsimply signing on a dotted line could
OL,16,Fcompletely change your circumstances.
OL,17,FWho could blame them?
